# UI components — prefer shadcn/ui

Before building custom UI primitives, check whether [shadcn/ui](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components/) already provides a suitable component.

## Workflow

1. **Check the catalog** — Browse [Components](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components/) for badges, dialogs, tables, tooltips, etc.
2. **Use what exists** — Import from `@/components/ui/<name>` when the component is already in the project.
3. **Add if missing** — Before running the CLI, confirm the component file does not already exist under `src/components/ui/`. If it does, **stop** — use the existing component; do not reinstall.

   Install only when the component is absent (do not hand-copy from docs unless the CLI is unavailable):

   ```bash
   npx shadcn@latest add <component>
   ```

   **Never override existing components.** Do not pass `--overwrite`, accept overwrite prompts, or re-run `add` to replace files that are already in the project. Existing components may have project-specific customizations — reinstalling would destroy them.

4. **Compose, don’t reinvent** — Extend shadcn components with `className`, variants, or composition. Do not recreate the same pattern with raw HTML + Tailwind.

## Examples

| Need | Do | Don’t |
|------|-----|--------|
| Status label | `<Badge variant="…">` | `<span className="rounded-full px-2 …">` |
| Modal / drawer | `Dialog`, `Sheet`, `Alert Dialog` | Custom fixed overlay + div |
| Data grid | `Table` (+ [Data Table](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components/data-table) when sorting/filtering) | Hand-rolled `<table>` styling |
| Tooltip | `Tooltip` | `title` only or custom popover div |
| Form field | `Field`, `Input`, `Label` | Unlabeled `<input>` with ad-hoc layout |

## Already installed

Components live under `src/components/ui/`. Check that folder before adding duplicates. Current set includes: `alert`, `badge`, `button`, `empty`, `field`, `input`, `label`, `separator`, `table`, `tooltip` (list may grow as components are added).

## When a custom component is OK

- No shadcn equivalent exists and the [registry directory](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/directory) has nothing suitable.
- The UI is **domain-specific** (e.g. `FileImport`, `ImportTransactionsTable`) — build it by **composing** shadcn primitives, not by replacing them with styled spans and divs.
